      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;DC vs AC in Van Life Workflows: How to Stretch Your Power Without Buying More&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;dc-vs-ac-in-van-life-workflows-how-to-stretch-your-power-without-buying-more&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#dc-vs-ac-in-van-life-workflows-how-to-stretch-your-power-without-buying-more&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Most people do not need more battery first. They need a better daily workflow. In van life, load habits can change stability just as much as hardware upgrades.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
